.TH "i915_vma_instance" 9 "i915_vma_instance" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i915_vma_instance \- return the singleton instance of the VMA
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct i915_vma *" i915_vma_instance
.BI "(struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj "  ","
.BI "struct i915_address_space *vm "  ","
.BI "const struct i915_ggtt_view *view "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "obj" 12
parent \fIstruct drm_i915_gem_object\fP to be mapped
.IP "vm" 12
address space in which the mapping is located
.IP "view" 12
additional mapping requirements
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBi915_vma_instance\fP looks up an existing VMA of the \fIobj\fP in the \fIvm\fP with
the same \fIview\fP characteristics. If a match is not found, one is created.
Once created, the VMA is kept until either the object is freed, or the
address space is closed.

Returns the vma, or an error pointer.
